================================================================================

This product is built with Flutter / Dart and depends on a number of
pub.dev packages distributed under MIT / BSD / Apache-2.0. See
`pubspec.yaml` and `pubspec.lock` for the complete list. The notable
ones requiring explicit notice are listed below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. libmpv  (used on Windows and Linux via just_audio_media_kit → media_kit)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
License: GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1+)
Upstream: https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv

This product uses libmpv as the audio playback backend on Windows and
Linux. On Windows, libmpv is bundled via the `media_kit_libs_windows_audio`
package, which ships an **audio-only** build of libmpv linked against an
LGPL build of FFmpeg (GPL-only encoders such as libx264 / libx265 are
NOT included). On Linux, libmpv is loaded dynamically from the system
package (e.g. `libmpv2` on Debian/Ubuntu).

LGPL section 4 compliance:
- libmpv is linked dynamically; users can replace the bundled DLL/SO with
  their own LGPL-compatible build.
- Source code for libmpv is available at the upstream URL above.
- Source code for the audio-only build can be obtained from:
  https://github.com/media-kit/libmpv-windows-audio-build
  https://github.com/media-kit/libmpv-android-audio-build

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. FFmpeg  (bundled with libmpv on Windows)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
License: GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1+)
Upstream: https://ffmpeg.org

The FFmpeg build bundled inside the audio-only libmpv DLL on Windows is
configured with `--disable-gpl`, so this distribution does NOT include
any GPL-only FFmpeg components. Source: same media-kit build repos
listed above.

